    <section id="about">
        <h2>About the Play</h2>
        <p>Romeo and Juliet is a tragedy by William Shakespeare, set in Verona, Italy. It tells the story of two young lovers from feuding families. Their love leads to their untimely deaths, which ultimately reconciles their warring families.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="characters">
        <h2>Main Characters</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Romeo Montague</strong>: The young son of the Montague family, deeply in love with Juliet.</li>
            <li><strong>Juliet Capulet</strong>: The young daughter of the Capulet family, who falls in love with Romeo.</li>
            <li><strong>Mercutio</strong>: Romeo's close friend, known for his witty and hot-headed nature.</li>
            <li><strong>Tybalt</strong>: Juliet's cousin, who dislikes the Montagues and seeks to fight them.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="themes">
        <h2>Themes in Romeo and Juliet</h2>
        <p>The play explores themes such as love, fate, family loyalty, and the consequences of hatred between families.</p>
    </section>

